<FIRST>r i PM-India-Riot     05-08 0187</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-India-Riot,0192</SECOND>
<HEAD>13 Killed, 50 Hurt in Islamic Festival Riot</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police opened fire when rival groups of
Moslems rioted during Islamic celebrations in the western town of
Mangrol and at least 13 people were killed, news reports said today.
   At least 50 people were injured in the clash Sunday night in
Mangrol, about 590 miles southwest of New Delhi, The Times of India
said.
   It was not immediately clear how many people died from police
fire and or when the Moslems battled each other with swords, steel
bars, stones and bottles, according to news reports.
   They did not say what prompted the clash in the remote area of
Gujarat state.
   United News of India and Press Trust of India said police opened
fire to quell the violence and that a deputy police superintendent
was seriously injured by the mob.
   The trouble started during celebrations of Eid al-Fitr, the
feast marking the end of the holy Ramadan month of fasting from
dawn to dusk.
   Moslems form 11 percent of India's 880 million people. Hindus
make up about 80 percent of the population.
