<FIRST>d a PM-BRF--StudentCrushed     05-08 0129</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Student Crushed,0133</SECOND>
<HEAD>Student Crushed by Vending Machine</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LAWRENCE, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man rocking a vending machine that
failed to release a can of soda was fatally injured when the
machine fell on him, authorities said.
   Lance Foster, 23, a University of Kansas student from
Stillwater, Okla., died Sunday while undergoing surgery for
injuries suffered in the Saturday accident, said Lt. Jeanne
Longaker of the university police.
   Foster told police he put 50 cents in the machine and began
rocking it back and forth when the machine did not release a can of
soda.
   Other students heard the noise and were able to lift the machine
off of Foster, Longaker said.
   Foster was taken to a Lawrence hospital and transported to the
medical center, where he died.
</TEXT>
