<FIRST>r i PM-Sweden-PlaneCrash 1stLd-Writethru a0477 05-08 0257</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Sweden-Plane Crash, 1st Ld-Writethru, a0477,0262</SECOND>
<HEAD>16 Believed Killed In Swedish Plane Crash</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New thruout to UPDATE with five Swedish politicians on passenger
list of plane that crashed. No Pickup.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OSKARSHAMN, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small plane crashed and exploded as
it landed at a coastal airport today, killing all 16 people
believed on board.
   Among the passengers reported on the twin-engine Beachcraft 99
plane were five Swedish politicians, a parliament spokeswoman said.
   But the fire that followed the explosion was so severe,
authorities were unable to determine if the 14 passengers and two
crewmen listed on the Holmstrom Flyg flight from Stockholm were
actually on board, said police duty officer Sigurd Gustafsson. ``No
one survived the crash,'' Gustafsson said.
   The politicians included three members of Parliament, Anna-Greta
Wohlin, Anders Andersson and Hans Rosengren; a former legislator,
Klas Renfeldt; and the former Stockholm party boss of the governing
Social Democrats, John-Olle Persson, the Swedish national radio
reported.
   The five were on a parliamentary fact-finding mission on
domestic telecommunications and air mail links, according to the
Parliament spokeswoman, who spoke on condition of anonymity.
   The plane hit the runway of Virkvarns Airport nose first, caught
fire, then exploded, witnesses told rescue workers.
   The cause of the crash was not immediately known. Gustafsson
said the weather was sunny and calm when the accident occurred at
the airport north of Oskarshamn, on the southeastern coast, 150
miles southwest of Stockholm.
   The propeller-driven aircraft belonged to the regional airline
Holmstrom Flyg, a family company that has seven small planes.
</TEXT>
