<TEXT>
   The State Department on Monday announced a $10
million contribution to the International Red Cross Movement to be
used for people displaced by the conflicts in Afghanistan and Sudan.
   The contribution was announced at ceremonies at American Red
Cross headquarters to observe the 125th anniversary of the signing
