<FIRST>r i AM--BRF--Iran-Drugs     05-08 0090</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM--BRF--Iran-Drugs,0093</SECOND>
<HEAD>Iran Hangs More Drug Smugglers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Iran on Monday hanged 15 convicted drug
traffickers, Tehran television reported.
   Monday's hangings brought to 558 the number of reported
executions of drug traffickers under a new law that took effect in
January. The law mandates the death sentence for possession of even
small quantities of drugs.
   Thousands of alleged pushers and addicts have been arrested
under the new law.
   Tehran radio reported last month that 792 drug smugglers and
addicts were rounded up in a two-day sweep.
