<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Britain-Museum     05-08 0099</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Britain-Museum,0101</SECOND>
<HEAD>Britain's Oldest Museum Appeals for Cash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>OXFORD, England (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Ashmolean, Britain's oldest museum,
launched an urgent appeal Monday to raise $5.3 million because of
cuts in government grants.
   Dr. Christopher White, the museum's director, said funds were
needed to offset an annual deficit of $158,650 and avoid closing
galleries, cutting staff and charging admission. He said lack of
funds had already forced the museum to close on Mondays.
   Entrance has been free since the museum opened in 1683. The
museum is a department of Oxford University and has collections of
antiquities, paintings and armor.
</TEXT>
