<HEAD>American Assaulted on Yangtze Boat Cruise Recovers</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An American who suffered a fractured skull when
he was attacked on a cruise down the Yangtze River a month ago has
recovered and discharged from a hospital, a newspaper reported
Monday.
   Derron Craft, of Bozeman, Mont., left a hospital in Wuhan, Hubei
province, on Saturday and was accompanied by his father and a U.S.
Embassy official on a flight to Beijing, the China Daily said.
   Craft, who began studying at the Beijing Languages Institute in
September, planned to return to the United States on Tuesday, the
embassy said.
   Craft, 23, was attacked in his sleep before dawn on April 8. The
identity of the assailant was unknown.
