<HEAD>Man Convicted Of Murder For Woman's Heart Attack Death During Rape</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS 2nd graf to UPDATE with jury finding aggravating circumstances.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PROVIDENCE, R.I. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A handyman was convicted of felony
murder Monday for the death of an elderly woman who suffered a
fatal heart attack while being raped on Christmas night 1987.
   Jeffrey Washington faces a mandatory sentence of life in prison,
and could be sentenced to life without parole because the jury
found the case involved aggravating circumstances, said Thomas
Connell, spokesman for the attorney general's office.
   The day after the attack, relatives found Alice Carcieri, 73,
whose legs had been amputated several years ago, dead in her bed.
Her wrists had been tied to the bed.
   Washington, 33, who sometimes did chores for Miss Carcieri, was
arrested four days later and confessed to police.
