<FIRST>r i AM-Philippines-Rebels     05-08 0191</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Philippines-Rebels,0197</SECOND>
<HEAD>Philippine Soldiers Kill 23 Guerrillas</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANILA, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Government forces killed at least 23
communist guerrillas in clashes around the country, the military
reported Tuesday.
   It gave no casualties of its own during the battles, which it
said took place in the 24 previous hours.
   In the biggest fight, soldiers attacked a camp of the New
People's Army at dusk Monday in the mountain town of Vintar in
Ilocos Norte province about 250 miles north of Manila.
   The two sides fought in sporadic clashes that continued Tuesday,
the army said. It said at least nine rebels were killed and two
captured.
   In Quezon province, about 100 miles southeast of Manila,
soldiers killed three rebels and captured two Monday, another
military report said.
   On Mindanao island, about 530 miles southeast of Manila,
troopers searching for six soldiers captured by rebels fought
insurgents Monday on the outskirts of Properidad in Agusan del Sur
province and killed seven guerrillas, the army said.
   In neighboring Surigao del Norte province, soldiers killed four
rebels near Malimono on Monday, the military said.
   The guerrillas have fought for 20 years to overthrow the
government.
</TEXT>
