<FIRST>s i BC-APN--FilipinoCommunists-Forces ADV21   05-08 0300</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-APN--Filipino Communists-Forces, ADV 21,0304</SECOND>
<HEAD>$Adv21</HEAD>
<HEAD>AGENCIES AND RADIO OUT</HEAD>
<HEAD>For Release Sunday, May 21</HEAD>
<HEAD>From AP Newsfeatures</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-APN--Filipino Communists</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   
   MANILA, Philippines (AP) _ Here are the major forces involved in
the Philippine Communist insurgency.
   Armed Forces of the Philippines: The 163,000-member volunteer
force is divided into four branches: Army, Navy, Air Force,
Philippine Constabulary and Marines. It is acknowledged to be the
poorest equipped military force among non-Communist nations of
Southeast Asia. It is augmented by thousands of civilian militamen
and anti-Communist vigilante groups, many of which are armed.
   Communist Party of the Philippines: The party was organized in
December 1968 by Prof. Jose Marie Sison. Its philosophy follows
that of the late Chinese leader Mao Tse-tung. The party claims
about 35,000 members but says its supporters number about 1 million
in a nation of 58 million.
   New Peoples Army: The New Peoples Army is the armed wing of the
Communist Party of the Philippines and operates in 65 of the 73
provinces. It was organized in 1969 from the remnants of the HUKs,
a pro-Soviet force that fought Japanese occupation troops in World
War II and then waged an unsuccessful, peasant insurgency in the
1950s and 1960s. The military estimates NPA strength at 23,000, but
the rebels claim 30,000. Both the military and the rebels say no
more than half the guerrillas are fully armed.
   National Democratic Front: This is a federation of 12 rebel
groups, including the Communist Party of the Philippines and the
New Peoples Army. The other 10 affiliates include left-wing
teachers, farmers, intellectuals, youth and Roman Catholic clergy
and laymen. It was organized by the party in an attempt to recruit
leftists who share Communist goals but who do not accept all
tenants of Marxism.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Sunday, May 21</NOTE>
