<FIRST>r f BC-SeafoodMerger     05-08 0159</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Seafood Merger,0166</SECOND>
<HEAD>Ocean Beauty Acquires Booth Fisheries</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SALT LAKE CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ocean Beauty Inc., a Seattle-based seafood
company, has acquired Booth Fisheries, merging the Utah operation
with the Salt Lake division of Ocean Beauty's Idaho Fish Co.
   Officials said the merged company, to be called Ocean Pride-Salt
Lake, will be the largest seafood distributor in the Mountain West
region.
   The company will be located in Salt Lake City at the present
Booth Fisheries plant, serving grocers, restaurants and food
distributors.
   Sales for Booth and Idaho Fish have increased rapidly, and ``the
merger gives us the financial and marketing strength that will
ensure that kind of growth,'' said Jack Whitney, former general
manager of Idaho Fish and general manager of the newly merged
fishery.
   Ocean Beauty has production facilities in Oregon, Washington and
Alaska and distribution outlets in seven western states.
   Booth Fisheries was established in Salt Lake in 1901 and was a
division of Booth Corp.
