<HEAD>Crop Futures Close Mostly Lower; Soybean Oil Surges</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Futures prices of grain and soybeans closed
mostly lower Monday on the Chicago Board of Trade amid rain
forecasts, but soybean oil futures surged on rumors of an impending
sale to the Soviet Union at subsidized prices.
   ``They want up to half a million (metric) tons but we don't
think the offer will be anything like that. They might get 100,000
tons,'' said Victor Lespinasse, a grain trader with Dean Witter
Reynolds Inc. in Chicago.
