per hundredweight.
   Soybeans for spot delivery were boosted by signs of active
farmer selling and other indications of tight nearby supplies. But
forecasts for rain in the Corn Belt on Monday night, Tuesday and
early next week kept pressure on most corn and soybean contracts.
   Wheat futures were narrowly mixed in cautious trading ahead of
Thursday's Agriculture Department estimate of the 1988-89 winter
wheat crop.
