<HEAD>Announces Sale of Central Hardware</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Interco Inc. announced Monday that it will sell
the Central Hardware Co. subsidiary for about $245 million.
   The sale to a group formed by Salomon Brothers Holding Co. Inc.
and an affiliate of Handy Andy Home Improvements Centers Inc. is
expected to be completed by June 12, the company said.
   Central Hardware operates 38 large do-it-yourself
home-improvement centers throughout the Midwest.
   The sale is part of the company's restructuring program, which
it adopted last year to foil a hostile takeover attempt from the
Rales brothers, a pair of Washington investors.
   In December, the company sold Londontown Corp., the manufacturer
of London Fog rainwear for $178 million.
   The company has said it would retain its Converse and Florsheim
footwear manufacturers and Broyhill and Lane furniture and home
furnishers as its four core businesses.
