<FIRST>r f BC-BraniffPilots     05-08 0094</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Braniff Pilots,0099</SECOND>
<HEAD>Braniff Pilots Ratify Contract Accord</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Braniff's 842-member airline pilots union
has ratified a contract agreement tentatively reached at the end of
April, an airline official said Monday.
   The agreement was the third major contract accord reached at the
airline since the start of the year, according to Robert T. Pike,
Braniff vice president for labor relations.
   The carrier released no details of the contract.
   Braniff earlier reached new contract agreements with the
Teamsters, representing the airline's agents and clerical
employees, and with the Flight Dispatchers Association.
</TEXT>
